LA INNOVACIÓN IMPLICA MUCHOS ASPECTOS DE NUESTRA SOCIEDAD: INVESTIGACIÓN EN LABORATORIOS, DESARROLLOS DE NUEVOS PRODUCTOS, SERVICIO Y LA CREACIÓN DE COMPAÑÍAS. EN LA ACTUALIDAD LA INNOVACIÓN SE ENFOCA EN PROBLEMAS RELACIONADOS AL MEDIO AMBIENTE, SALUD, PRÁCTICAS CULTURALES, COMUNICACIÓN Y TECNOLOGÍA. ESTE CURSO ES PARTE DE UN CONCEPTO AMPLIO QUE INVOLUCRA LA CREACIÓN DE UNA NUEVA ÁREA DE INVESTIGACIÓN PARA INNOVACIÓN Y EMPRENDIMIENTO, EL DESARROLLO DE LÍNEAS EMBLEMÁTICAS DE INVESTIGACIÓN Y LA IMPLEMENTACIÓN DE ACTIVIDADES ESTRATÉGICAS DENTRO DEL ALCANCE DE LA SOCIEDAD DEL CONOCIMIENTO. EL ESFUERZO CONJUNTO Y SINÉRGICO DE YACHAY TECH CON DISTINTAS UNIVERSIDADES Y CON COMPAÑÍAS NACIONALES E INTERNACIONALES PROMOVIÓ LA CREACIÓN DE ESTE CURSO PARA FOMENTAR LA CULTURA EMPRENDEDORA EN ECUADOR. POR LO TANTO, ESTE CURSO ARTICULA UN ESPACIO DE INNOVACIÓN QUE BUSCA SER LA SEMILLA DE PROYECTOS DE INCUBADORA DE EMPRENDIMIENTO EN YACHAY TECH.

FOCUSES ON FURTHERING A MORE COMPLEX GRAMMAR AND WRITING STRUCTURES. STUDENTS EXPAND THEIR KNOWLEDGE OF VERB TENSES (CONTINUOUS AND PERFECT TENSES), SENTENCE STRUCTURE (CONDITIONALS, TRANSITIONS, DEPENDENT CLAUSES, ETC.), PARAGRAPH STRUCTURE, AND 3-PARAGRAPH ESSAYS. ESSAY WRITING INCLUDES AN INTRODUCTION PARAGRAPH WITH A THESIS STATEMENT, BODY PARAGRAPHS WITH LOGICAL SUPPORT, AND A CONCLUSION PARAGRAPH. READING SKILLS INCLUDE IDENTIFYING MAIN IDEAS, SUPPORTING DETAILS, INFERENCES, AND VOCABULARY IN CONTEXT.

FOCUSES ON REINFORCING GRAMMAR AND WRITING SKILLS WITH REVIEWS OF VERB TENSES, SENTENCE STRUCTURE, AND PARAGRAPH/ESSAY STRUCTURE. NEW GRAMMAR TOPICS ARE LIMITED TO PASSIVE, GERUNDS, INFINITIVES, THIRD CONDITIONALS, AND NOUN/ADJECTIVE CLAUSES. STUDENTS EXPAND THEIR ESSAY WRITING SKILLS TO COMPLETE A 5- PARAGRAPH ESSAY, WHICH INCLUDES SUMMARIZING, PARAPHRASING, AND QUOTING. ACADEMIC READING SKILLS CONTINUE TO BE WORKING ON WITH INCREASINGLY DIFFICULTY.

A PROJECT-ORIENTED COURSE ALLOWS STUDENTS TO APPLY THEIR ACQUIRED ACADEMIC ENGLISH SKILLS ON INDIVIDUAL AND GROUP ASSIGNMENTS. EAP-I FOCUSES ON INTEGRATION OF THE FOUR SKILLS ON VARIOUS PROJECTS WITH A SPECIFIC FOCUS ON SCIENTIFIC EXPRESSION IN ENGLISH. STUDENTS LEARN TO UNDERSTAND THE MAIN IDEAS OF FAMILIAR AND EVERY DAY SUBJECTS AS WELL AS SOME SCIENTIFIC MATERIAL. THEY CAN COMFORTABLY SHARE INFORMATION ABOUT THEIR OWN LIVES, HISTORIES, AND GOALS AS WELL AS DISCUSS AND UNDERSTAND CONVERSATION ABOUT CURRENT EVENTS. THEY MAY, AT TIMES, NEED CLARIFICATION OR REPEATED/SLOW DELIVERY OF INFORMATION, BUT THEY CAN MAINTAIN IN-DEPTH DISCUSSIONS ABOUT TOPICS THAT ARE FAMILIAR OR OF INTEREST TO THEM. THEY CAN READ STANDARD NEWSPAPERS, MAGAZINES, AND PERSONAL/BUSINESS CORRESPONDENCE AS WELL AS SCIENTIFIC MATERIAL WRITTEN FOR LAY PERSONS. THEY CAN WRITE USING SOME BASIC SCIENTIFIC PATTERNS AND VOCABULARY IN THE TARGET LANGUAGE. THEY CAN SPONTANEOUSLY PRODUCE IN ENGLISH INFORMATION – WRITTEN AND SPOKEN – ABOUT THE BASICS OF SCIENCE. THEY CAN SUMMARIZE AND PARAPHRASE INFORMATION FROM A VARIETY OF SOURCES AND GIVE THEIR OPINION ON THAT MATERIAL.

FOCUSES ON REFINING ACADEMIC AND COMMUNICATIVE SKILLS. WORKING TOWARDS PROFICIENCY IN ARTICULATING, EXPRESSING, AND SUPPORTING VIEWPOINTS, STUDENTS LEARN A VARIETY OF APPROACHES IN WRITING AND SPEAKING, WHICH INCLUDE PERSUASIVE, COMPARATIVE, AND INFORMATIVE TECHNIQUES. THIS COURSE IS WORKSHOP-BASED, MEANING STUDENTS WORK INDIVIDUALLY AND COLLABORATIVELY TO ACHIEVE THEIR GOALS AND REFINE THEIR SKILLS. STUDENTS ENGAGE WITH A VARIETY OF TEXTS, AND THE COURSE CUMULATES IN A STUDENT DEVELOPED RESEARCH PROJECT THAT THEY WILL CARRY OUT, ANALYZE, AND PRESENT.
